<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-10-24.S3W-16678.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa1024.htm#3">Sex Offenders</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-10-24.S3W-16678.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80284" speakername="Richard Baker (North East Scotland) (Lab)" spid="S3W-16678" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa1024.htm#3">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive in which (a) prisons and (b) young offenders&rsquo; institutions the Sex Offender Treatment Programme was run in each of the last five years.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2008-10-24.S3W-16678.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80341" speakername="Kenny MacAskill" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-08/wa1024.htm#3">

  <p>I have asked Mike Ewart, Chief Executive of the Scottish Prison Service to respond. His response is as follows:</p>

  <p>Sex Offender Treatment Programmes (SOTP) have been delivered in (a) HM Prisons Peterhead, Barlinnie and Edinburgh and (b) HM YOI Polmont in each of the last five years.</p>

</reply>


